The WNBA Has Its Own 3-Point Revolution

The much discussed 3-point revolution is not limited to the NBA. While the WNBA has historically relied more on the 3-point shot than the NBA, the increased arc distance in 2013 and the recent surge in NBA 3-point attempts has seen that relationship flip. If recent trends continue, don't be surprised if the WNBA catches up soon.

tspan.tspan: Who is driving the surge in 3-point attempts?

flowRoot.flowPara: Three teams—Seattle Storm, Phoenix Mercury, and Washington Mystics—are leading the way, stretching defenses with multiple 3-point shooters. In 2018, all three teams attempted 3-pointers at nearly the same pace as the 2017-2018 NBA league average.
